        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer8804432" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8848993145906254538">Normally, I hate the word &quot;sensual&quot; because it reminds me of essential oils and the phrase &quot;taking a lover,&quot; and lying about on the divan whilst eating succulent grapes dripping with the juices of summer, but this collection contains essays about the senses, so I think the word actually applies in this case. If I&apos;m remembering correctly, this is Calvino&apos;s last book. He was going to write five essays for five senses, but he died before he got there. The essay on taste is my favorite. It&apos;s about s</span>
  <span id="freeText8848993145906254538" style="display:none">Normally, I hate the word "sensual" because it reminds me of essential oils and the phrase "taking a lover," and lying about on the divan whilst eating succulent grapes dripping with the juices of summer, but this collection contains essays about the senses, so I think the word actually applies in this case. If I'm remembering correctly, this is Calvino's last book. He was going to write five essays for five senses, but he died before he got there. The essay on taste is my favorite. It's about spices and the desire/repulsion for cannibalism, and it's well--very sensual. </span>
  <a data-text-id="8848993145906254538" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

