<div id="review_2054349286" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2054349286" />
    <a title="Jeff Jackson" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/811567-jeff-jackson"><img alt="Jeff Jackson" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1531248217p2/811567.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2054349286?book_show_action=true">Oct 28, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jeff Jackson" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jeff Jackson" href="/user/show/811567-jeff-jackson">Jeff Jackson</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2054349286" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6497342776647939894">The rating is in relation to other Calvino books, an arbitrary marker to myself. The three tales here all offer their pleasures, each one focusing on one of the senses, the finest being the title story about taste and the next best the tale about the king in his palace, alert to every stray sounds. An unfinished and minor work and not the place to start, but still shot through with wonder. <br/>3.5 stars </span>

          </span>
        </div>


