<div id="review_2431196967" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2431196967" />
    <a title="Ed Erwin" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1411444-ed-erwin"><img alt="Ed Erwin" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1625415118p2/1411444.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2431196967?book_show_action=true">Jun 24, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ed Erwin" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ed Erwin" href="/user/show/1411444-ed-erwin">Ed Erwin</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1411444-ed-erwin?shelf=short-story">short-story</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2431196967" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15542932096245912678">Calvino, while great, is hit-or-miss for me, and this was mostly a miss. The final story in the collection, which was written a full decade before the other two, is the most interesting. Even though that story is quite short, it is really itself 3 separate stories all about death and the relation between the scent of flesh and obsession. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


